    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Magnolia grandiflora, native to the Atlantic Coastal plain forests from Virginia to Texas. It has a creamy white sapwood, with a greenish or sometimes purplish tinge, and is used for joinery, doors, furniture, veneer, and paneling.</Note_Text>
